Im  years old immunosuppressed one year post kidney transplant and I caught Covid whilst recovering from uro septicemia only one month ago had both of my Pfizer jabs and have been nothing but careful and isolated as much as humanly possible but somehow one of my family must have been a carrier and passed it to me upon visiting through no fault of their own

One month in the hospital isnt the longest time but I truly have to say that it has been one of the most harrowing experiences of my life more so than my initial bilateral nephrectomy both kidneys removed as they were riddled with chronic kidney disease  and Transplant both mentally and physically I wouldnt wish it on a single human being so please protect others 

Fortunately today although still in my hospital bed my oxygen levels have recovered well and I am on the mend and should be going home in a matter of a week or two I am incredibly lucky everybody please I beg of you stay safe for your own sakes and everybody elses

A huge issue with the media is that there isnt enough talk around what happens whilst you have Covid it is largely explained as either mild symptoms similar to that of a cold or ventilation leading to in many circumstances inevitable death but what happens in between is solitary confinement oxygen not circulating around your body leading to confusion and delusion a constant sense of anxiety the risk of organs including your brain taking permanent damage and failing painful coughing the ability to breathe simply gone your lungs feeling like they are full of wasps stinging due to the crackling of fluid as it grates on the damage and inflammation that this illness causes the inability to move and bodily aches that rival that of going  rounds in a boxing ring and not being allowed to defend yourself

DO NOT take Covid lightly it is truly truly horrific and I am incredibly thankful to be alive to try to raise awareness of it by writing this comment

well hello future people here is something to give you an idea of life during corona and why nobody likes it

imagine one day your on your phone when your parents call you over Youve heard of the coronavirus but you think that its only going to be a small thing like a cold Your parents tell you to sit down at the kitchen table and your brother looks over at you looking as confused as you felt So your dad starts Your school is closed and there will be a half day tomorrow Your mom cuts in Then there will be a three week break Says your dad You gasp no way you think Youve heard of schools closing but you didnt think it would happen to you You and your dad go shopping that night laughing and saying that we were panic shopping 
The next day you go to school You and your friends laugh joking about if the schools closed for the whole year You didnt even think it was possible  Your school gives you books so you have something to do during the three weeks of break You say goodbye to your friends not knowing that it would be your last day in elementary school Not knowing that it would be the last time that you would see most of your friends for a year and a half 
When you get home your dad makes you walk home he normally picks you up and drives you through your short neighborhood When you get home he tells you that there is a high chance you have coronavirus on you You go upstairs to shower and change feeling like your in a movie 
From now on every time you go out you must wear an uncomfortable mask You must swerve to not go close to people Hold your breath for long periods of time when you dont have a mask on next to people Your whole life is changed Your parents choose the school option where you have no zooms so you havent seen all your friends in a year Your whole life is flipped upside down and in a bad way

Well Thats my story I guess Thanks for reading

You can buy P half mask respirators online About to bucks Make sure the half mask comes with P magenta color filters otherwise you need to buy filters separately P filter cartridges provide near virus filtration and if you are fit tested a specialized leak test required by OSHA then they do provide Make sure the half mask fits you properly A normal adult size face will be a large size Women might be a medium size The P filters are HEPA filters and they will last a very long time unless youre working in a very dusty environment They should last at least a year or so but you can buy a pair of new filters for about Wear it when you go into any public building It will save your life Make sure you are clean shaven no beards or stubble otherwise the mask will not seal to your face and virus can get through Perform a positive and negative pressure check on the respirator when you first put it on this is a basic selfseal check you can research online to ensure proper sealing These respirators have been designed and researched by NIOSH for decades and they are required by OSHA You can make and attach a simple loose cloth cover for the exhalation valve to prevent coughing droplets from being released Use caution if you have preexisting respiratory health issues as wearing a respirator does add some resistance to normal breathing but you will find half mask respirators to be very comfortable and much easier to breathe through and cooler than most masks and face coverings because of the exhaust valve Make sure to keep your respirator clean inside using sanitary wipes and make sure the membrane valves are taken care of and are not damaged because they can tear easily Store your respirator in a Ziploc bag Do not share your respirator with others Half mask respirators can be completely dismantled and cleaned but this only needs to be done occasionally

Coronavirus disease COVID is an infectious disease caused by a newly discovered coronavirus Most people who fall sick with COVID will experience mild to moderate symptoms and recover without special treatment HOW IT SPREADS The virus that causes COVID is mainly transmitted through droplets generated when an infected person coughs sneezes or exhales These droplets are too heavy to hang in the air and quickly fall on floors or surfaces You can be infected by breathing in the virus if you are within close proximity of someone who has COVID or by touching a contaminated surface and then your eyes nose or mouth Coronaviruses are a large family of zoonotic viruses that cause illness ranging from the common cold to severe respiratory diseases Zoonotic means these viruses are able to be transmitted from animals to humans There are several coronaviruses known to be circulating in different animal populations that have not yet infected humans Animals are the most likely source of the COVID It is possible that the COVID virus originated from animals before it infected humans However the specific source of COVID virus is yet to be confirmed COVID is the most recent to make the jump to human infection If COVID is spreading in your community stay safe by taking some simple precautions such as physical distancing wearing a mask keeping rooms well ventilated avoiding crowds cleaning your hands and coughing into a bent elbow or tissue Check local advice from where you live and work Maintain at least a metre distance between yourself and others to reduce your risk of infection when they cough sneeze or speak Avoid touching your eyes nose and mouth Hands touch many surfaces and can pick up viruses Once contaminated hands can transfer the virus to your eyes nose or mouth From there the virus can enter your body and infect you Clean and disinfect surfaces frequently especially those which are regularly touched such as door handles faucets and phone screens And also for those who are a fan of shopping online once you receive your package that is being delivered dont forget to disinfect your package well Regularly and thoroughly clean your hands with an alcoholbased hand rub or wash them with soap and water This eliminates germs including viruses that may be on your hands proper nutrition and hydration improve health and immunity People living with chronic illnesses who have suspected or confirmed COVID may need support with their mental health and diet to ensure they keep in good health Seek counseling and psychosocial support from appropriately trained health care professionals and also communitybased lay and peer counsellors Dont forget to Drink enough water every day Make sure to take your vitamins Eat fresh and unprocessed foods every day Do not overcook vegetables and fruits as this can lead to the loss of important vitamins When using canned or dried vegetables and fruits choose varieties without added salt or sugar Avoid eating out and instead just eat at home to reduce your rate of contact with other people and lower your chance of being exposed to COVID And those are just some of the information about the Covid
